OL,3,CPembrokeshire could face 21% rise in
OL,4,Ccouncil tax for 2024-25 financial year
OL,6,FResidents in could face a 21% hike in
OL,7,Ftheir for the forthcoming financial
OL,8,Fyear, which could cost an average
OL,9,Fhousehold nearly #300 more a year.
OL,11,FCabinet members at Pembrokeshire
OL,12,FCounty Council will meet on Monday
OL,13,Fmorning, 12 February, to discuss and
OL,14,Frecommend three possible options for a
OL,15,Fcouncil tax increase.
OL,17,FThese range from 16.31%, 18.94% and a
OL,18,F20.98% hike.
